                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_cadæg" xml:lang="os"><form type="lemma"><orth>cadæg</orth></form><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>тихий</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>медленный</q></tr></sense></sense><re><form type="lemma"><orth>cadæggaj</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>понемногу</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>little by little</q></tr></sense></re><exampleGrp><example><quote>cadæggaj jyl abady (bæxyl)</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>потихоньку садится (на коня)</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>[s/he] is mounting a horse little by little</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>IV 139</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example><quote>cadæggaj jyl abady (bæxyl)</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>потихоньку садится (на коня)</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>[s/he] is mounting a horse little by little</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>IV 139</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Прош. причастик от глагола *%icajyn%i, снабженное суффиксом %iæg%i (%icad-æg%i = <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>čyāta-ka</w></mentioned>). Глагол *%icajyn%i (<mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>čyā-</w> <gloss><q>покоиться</q></gloss></mentioned> сохранился только в сращении с превербом %iæn%i-: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æncajyn"/> : <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æncad"/> ‘покоиться’. Такую же морфологическую структуру, как %icadæg%i (прош. причастие + %iæg%i), имеют <ref type="xr" target="#entry_syǧdæg"/> ‘чистый’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_lystæg"/> ‘мелкий’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cærdæg"/> ‘живой’ и др. У поэта <bibl><author>Коста</author></bibl> (в черновых рукописях) встречается также форма %iæncadæg%i. Взятое без суффикса -%iæg%i осетинское <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/> <w>cad-</w></mentioned> точно соответствует <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>čyāta-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>šāta-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/> <w>šāt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>šād</w> <gloss><q>радостный</q></gloss></mentioned> и пр. См. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æncon"/>.%n<bibl><author>Morgenstierne</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_NTS"/><biblScope>XII 267</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Past participle form of the verb %icajyn%i with the suffix %iæg%i (%icad-æg%i = <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>čyāta-ka</w></mentioned>). The verb *%icajyn%i (<mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>čyā-</w> <gloss><q>repose</q></gloss></mentioned> remained only bound with the preverb %iæn%i-: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æncajyn"/> : <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æncad"/> ‘repose’. The same morphological structure, as %icadæg%i (past participle + %iæg%i), is found in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_syǧdæg"/> ‘pure’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_lystæg"/> ‘small’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cærdæg"/> ‘alive’ etc. The poet <bibl><author>Kosta</author></bibl> had (in drafts) the form %iæncadæg%i. The Ossetic word <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/> <w>cad-</w></mentioned> without suffix -%iæg%i exactly corresponds <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>čyāta-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>šāta-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/> <w>šāt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>šād</w> <gloss><q>happy</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. See <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æncon"/>.%n<bibl><author>Morgenstierne</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_NTS"/><biblScope>XII 267</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>